description: Let Product[1+Sum[b(i,j) x^(i*j),{i,1,Infinity}],{j,1,Infinity}]=1+Sum[c(n) x^n,{n,1,Infinity}], where b(i,j) is plus or minus one and c(n) is plus or minus one or zero. Furthermore, let b(1,1)=1 (for definiteness). Then, for a given n, a(n) is the number of ways in which the coefficients b(i,j) i<=n, j<=n can be chosen.
